						<summary>

						<p>Broken Slab (No. 6) lying near the <hi rend="italic">hōmakuṇḍa</hi> in the Pañchaliṅgēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Bukka I, 1363 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 128[6], • • • krit, Śrāvaṇa ba. 6, [Tuesday].</hi> If the cyclic year was Śōbhakṛit, the details regularly correspond to <hi rend="bold">1363 A.D., August 1.</hi> The Śaka year was current. </p>						

						<p>The proper right portion of the slab is broken. It registers a gift to god Mārkaṇḍēśvara probably by Gaṇapa whose father (name lost) was a <hi rend="italic">sēnabōva.</hi> <hi rend="bold">Maleya-daṇṇāyaka</hi> was governing <hi rend="bold">Bārakūru-rājya.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
